WEBVTT

00:29.217 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:34.972
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:34.973 --> 00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:43.148 --> 00:46.150
ETA
1 HOUR

00:46.151 --> 00:47.277
One hour.

01:21.895 --> 01:23.230
BEN

01:24.940 --> 01:27.400
Hey, Ben. I'm driving.

01:27.401 --> 01:30.277
-  Do you have your passport?
- My passport? Uh…

01:30.278 --> 01:33.239
It's in my room, in the third drawer. Why?

01:33.240 --> 01:35.783
Get your passport
and come to the airport.

01:35.784 --> 01:37.660
We have to go to the States right now.

01:37.661 --> 01:40.037
What? What are you saying?

01:42.207 --> 01:43.917
Why do we have to go?

01:44.626 --> 01:46.336
Come to my office.

01:50.382 --> 01:54.677
ANIMATOR SEONU CHAN

01:54.678 --> 01:55.761
EPISODE 6

01:59.724 --> 02:01.183
Hello?

02:01.184 --> 02:02.268
Express delivery?

02:02.269 --> 02:03.853
I'll head there right away.

02:03.854 --> 02:07.565
Ben, I just got here.
I'm going to receive my passport.

02:07.566 --> 02:10.776
Hurry. There aren't many seats left
for the 7:30 flight.

02:22.122 --> 02:24.415
- Hey.
-  Hurry up! We don't have time.

02:24.416 --> 02:25.584
I'm heading inside now.

02:26.126 --> 02:27.252
Okay.

02:32.507 --> 02:35.677
HANG IN THERE!

02:37.387 --> 02:40.098
Hello. This way, please.

02:42.058 --> 02:43.351
DESIGNER SONG HARAN

02:45.854 --> 02:47.563
ANIMATOR SEONU CHAN

02:47.564 --> 02:50.900
Dear passengers,
this is Korea Air, Flight 202

02:50.901 --> 02:53.403
headed for Los Angeles
International Airport.

02:53.904 --> 02:55.738
Please wear your seatbelts

02:55.739 --> 02:59.992
and switch all electronic devices
to airplane mode.

03:04.247 --> 03:05.707
MISSED CALL
ANIMATOR SEONU CHAN

03:07.375 --> 03:09.668
Mr. Park, did you hear from Mr. Seonu?

03:09.669 --> 03:10.670
Oh?

03:13.048 --> 03:17.468
He said he'd take
the earliest flight to the US.

03:17.469 --> 03:19.054
He must be gone already.

03:22.933 --> 03:24.935
YOUR PHOTOS ARE READY FOR PICKUP.
HOBAK PHOTO STUDIO

03:25.977 --> 03:28.021
The project's suspended?

03:28.939 --> 03:30.397
Producer Ben said

03:30.398 --> 03:33.400
there were major executive changes
at the US headquarters.

03:33.401 --> 03:38.113
And the new decision-maker said
they'll halt all ongoing projects.

03:38.114 --> 03:40.533
The project's up in the air right now.

04:02.597 --> 04:05.266
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

04:05.267 --> 04:07.017
They really left?

04:07.018 --> 04:08.227
The entire staff?

04:08.228 --> 04:11.188
The production team left in a hurry
after hearing the news.

04:11.189 --> 04:13.107
I'll share any updates if I receive any.

04:13.108 --> 04:15.360
This is just so sudden.

04:17.654 --> 04:20.614
All animation work
will be on hold for now.

04:20.615 --> 04:23.450
We'll start meetings
for the next season tomorrow,

04:23.451 --> 04:24.786
so get ready.

04:25.370 --> 04:26.495
Team 1 meeting's over.

04:26.496 --> 04:28.247
- Call Team 2.
- All right.

04:28.248 --> 04:30.959
-  Thank you.
- Thank you.

04:39.467 --> 04:41.927
Wow. Weren't we pretty close?

04:41.928 --> 04:43.929
He could've at least sent a message.

04:43.930 --> 04:45.848
His phone's off, too.

04:45.849 --> 04:48.183
He was using
a temporary phone here, right?

04:48.184 --> 04:50.270
Pureum, he's not using
this number in the States?

04:51.354 --> 04:54.106
- Chan isn't coming here anymore, then?
-  Hmm…

04:54.107 --> 04:56.275
I feel like he'll come back soon, though.

04:56.276 --> 04:58.444
Why? Did he tell you something?

04:58.445 --> 04:59.653
No,

04:59.654 --> 05:03.033
but I feel like he'll solve everything
and come back soon.

05:03.742 --> 05:07.828
Chan doesn't seem like the type
to just end things like this.

05:07.829 --> 05:10.874
Right. It hasn't been confirmed
that it's canceled yet.

05:11.791 --> 05:14.085
Chan might already be pretty close

05:14.711 --> 05:16.712
to the new person in charge.

05:16.713 --> 05:20.883
You're right. He'll solve it straight away
and return with a surprise.

05:20.884 --> 05:23.510
What kind of surprise?

05:23.511 --> 05:25.722
For example…

05:28.808 --> 05:31.102
What's this huge box? Fabric samples?

05:31.770 --> 05:33.938
The Chan you ordered is here!

05:36.900 --> 05:37.983
Ta-da!

05:37.984 --> 05:40.569
He could appear like a magic trick.

05:40.570 --> 05:42.196
That's possible.

05:42.197 --> 05:44.407
That does suit him.

05:46.368 --> 05:50.121
Seonu Chan really is something.
He's making us laugh even when he's away.

05:50.789 --> 05:52.665
Geez.

05:52.666 --> 05:54.083
I really miss him.

06:04.678 --> 06:06.011
Hmm…

06:07.347 --> 06:10.308
A reinterpretation
of Nana Atelier's early outfits.

06:12.644 --> 06:14.979
Oh, my. This is going to work.

06:14.980 --> 06:16.564
The new Haran's killing it lately.

06:17.273 --> 06:20.317
You have digital files
of videos from the '70s, right?

06:20.318 --> 06:21.944
I'll share them with you now.

06:21.945 --> 06:23.196
Ah.

06:24.239 --> 06:28.451
Okay. Then let's build on that
and do some more research…

06:29.911 --> 06:30.912
Tsk.

06:31.830 --> 06:36.959
I'm sure Chan will come back
in a few days, saying "Surprise!"

06:36.960 --> 06:38.502
So…  Don't worry.

06:38.503 --> 06:41.214
But if he contacts you
before then, tell us right away.

06:42.340 --> 06:45.093
- What?
- Wouldn't he contact you first?

06:45.969 --> 06:47.970
You haven't been screening your windows.

06:47.971 --> 06:50.140
I know it's because of Chan.

06:50.890 --> 06:52.474
I'm very perceptive, you know.

06:55.812 --> 06:57.396
Hello?

06:57.397 --> 06:58.605
New Haran?

06:58.606 --> 06:59.941
It's mine.

07:00.358 --> 07:01.442
Yes, Ms. Kim.

07:01.443 --> 07:04.154
I was going to visit on the weekend.

07:05.196 --> 07:07.407
My phone doesn't seem to be ringing…

07:20.462 --> 07:21.504
ANIMATOR SEONU CHAN

07:24.299 --> 07:25.632
LOS ANGELES TIME DIFFERENCE

07:25.633 --> 07:27.342
SEOUL IS 17 HOURS AHEAD OF LOS ANGELES

07:27.343 --> 07:29.428
It would be morning there.

07:29.429 --> 07:31.181
HAVE YOU ARRIVED YET?

07:50.617 --> 07:51.659
Darn it.

07:52.619 --> 07:53.703
Did I fall asleep here?

07:54.537 --> 07:55.705
What time is it?

07:56.706 --> 07:58.916
I must be crazy.

08:23.775 --> 08:25.567
Innovative materials?

08:25.568 --> 08:27.236
You mean using new materials?

08:27.237 --> 08:31.199
Yes. The same beauty,
but more eco-friendly.

08:31.825 --> 08:35.744
We'll recreate
one of our archive's 1979 silk pleated set

08:35.745 --> 08:38.038
with fermented protein fabric.

08:38.039 --> 08:41.543
It'll be eco-friendly
and maintain its elegant mood.

08:42.126 --> 08:45.170
Nice. Maison has been using
new materials these days, too.

08:45.171 --> 08:48.299
We could target eco-conscious consumers
who don't buy clothes.

08:48.883 --> 08:50.301
That's what I mean.

08:50.927 --> 08:52.094
We can't.

08:52.095 --> 08:56.640
Nana Atelier built its name
on silk and cashmere craftsmanship.

08:56.641 --> 08:58.684
Using unstable, unverified materials

08:58.685 --> 09:01.854
may jeopardize our launch schedule
as well as brand trust.

09:01.855 --> 09:04.898
The show is meant to showcase
the brand's vision.

09:04.899 --> 09:08.026
Young consumers care about
both style and sustainability.

09:08.027 --> 09:09.778
We should adapt to the times.

09:09.779 --> 09:11.530
It's all about
value-based consumption now.

09:11.531 --> 09:13.240
If we don't, we'll get discarded.

09:13.241 --> 09:15.492
Customer trust comes first for our brand.

09:15.493 --> 09:17.661
Moving away from our premium materials

09:17.662 --> 09:20.289
will risk losing the loyalty
of our longtime customers.

09:20.290 --> 09:23.417
I know trust is important,
but the world has changed.

09:23.418 --> 09:26.545
A brand that doesn't change
is even more risky.

09:26.546 --> 09:28.298
Taking a risk is more dangerous.

09:28.882 --> 09:30.549
We already have a packed schedule.

09:30.550 --> 09:34.469
It won't be wise to make a risky move
that may disrupt our timeline.

09:34.470 --> 09:35.680
- I--
-  Stop.

09:36.514 --> 09:38.558
I welcome
discussions like this anytime.

09:39.309 --> 09:42.936
Let's put some more thought into this
and discuss it again next time.

09:42.937 --> 09:44.439
- Yes, ma'am.
- Okay.

09:45.064 --> 09:46.148
I prepared everything.

09:46.149 --> 09:49.611
There's something else.
I received good news this morning.

09:54.032 --> 09:55.825
What? Do you want to perform or something?

09:57.327 --> 09:58.493
Oh…

09:58.494 --> 10:01.706
No, I just needed to adjust my outfit.

10:03.333 --> 10:05.626
The pre-order stock
for the Lafayette coats

10:05.627 --> 10:07.961
have already sold out.

10:07.962 --> 10:09.838
We received additional orders.

10:09.839 --> 10:11.131
That's amazing!

10:11.132 --> 10:12.925
That's great news.

10:12.926 --> 10:16.011
Good. Make sure everything stays on track
until they're shipped.

10:16.012 --> 10:17.347
Yes, ma'am.

10:21.517 --> 10:24.062
Hey. Was I wrong?

10:24.646 --> 10:26.647
Using materials
that didn't exist back then

10:26.648 --> 10:27.981
is what we call reinterpretation.

10:27.982 --> 10:29.274
You're right.

10:29.275 --> 10:31.109
The fermented protein fabric idea
was good.

10:31.110 --> 10:32.861
Then why was Mr. Yeon like that?

10:32.862 --> 10:36.073
"No. Customer trust comes first."

10:36.074 --> 10:38.200
"We can't risk customer loyalty."

10:40.536 --> 10:41.620
What?

10:47.961 --> 10:50.295
Here's the list of outfits
for tomorrow's VIP fitting.

10:50.296 --> 10:51.756
Please get everything ready.

10:55.593 --> 10:58.888
It's my job to bridge the gap
between the artist's vision and reality.

11:02.016 --> 11:05.937
He cares so much about our family,
but why is he so strict with me?

11:06.479 --> 11:08.523
I'm not bothered at all.

11:13.361 --> 11:15.363
She seems incredibly bothered, right?

11:16.155 --> 11:17.323
Totally.

11:17.907 --> 11:20.617
But aren't disagreements like that
common during meetings?

11:20.618 --> 11:24.037
That's what I mean.
Why is she suddenly so upset?

11:24.038 --> 11:25.706
I don't understand the reason.

11:25.707 --> 11:26.708
The reason…

11:27.458 --> 11:28.793
Hmm.

11:37.468 --> 11:42.849
I'm sure Chan will come back
in a few days, saying "Surprise!"

11:44.267 --> 11:45.767
When did you get here?

11:45.768 --> 11:47.311
You should've called.

11:47.312 --> 11:49.021
Did everything go okay?

11:51.649 --> 11:52.859
Excuse me?

11:53.818 --> 11:56.654
Oh… Sorry, I mistook you for someone else.

12:04.954 --> 12:06.997
Am I sleep deprived?

12:06.998 --> 12:09.666
WAITING FOR GODOT

12:13.171 --> 12:15.631
Hello.

12:16.507 --> 12:18.175
Hey, you're here.

12:18.176 --> 12:20.635
Is Genius still not eating?

12:21.721 --> 12:23.973
He doesn't seem to have
an appetite either.

12:24.557 --> 12:26.809
- Sit. I'll make you coffee.
- Okay.

12:34.692 --> 12:35.693
Huh?

12:36.611 --> 12:39.237
You're not sitting
in your seat of seven years?

12:39.238 --> 12:41.783
I want to sit here today.

12:51.209 --> 12:52.627
It feels like there's a hole.

12:54.212 --> 12:58.591
My heart feels so empty.
It's like wind is blowing through it.

13:00.301 --> 13:04.389
I feel like he'll burst in any second,
shouting "Mr. Park!"

13:05.223 --> 13:08.601
and going on and on about something.

13:12.897 --> 13:13.980
Mr. Park!

13:15.316 --> 13:16.567
Did you have fun? Huh?

13:17.360 --> 13:18.903
Genius. Hey.

13:32.250 --> 13:35.001
You forgot your meds again, didn't you?

13:35.002 --> 13:37.505
I really need to scold you.

13:39.048 --> 13:42.884
I feel like I'll start hearing him
nag me again.

13:42.885 --> 13:45.345
- When will he come back?
- Oh?

13:45.346 --> 13:46.806
What? Is he here?

13:48.808 --> 13:49.933
Donggu.

13:49.934 --> 13:51.393
Hello.

13:51.394 --> 13:54.604
Is Chan still not back from Gyeongju?

13:54.605 --> 13:56.189
I can't reach him.

13:56.190 --> 13:57.566
He went to the US.

13:57.567 --> 13:58.818
What?

14:29.056 --> 14:30.099
Hadam!

14:32.226 --> 14:34.811
Don't you usually go
to the study lounge on this day?

14:34.812 --> 14:36.104
Yes.

14:36.105 --> 14:39.983
It's so nice to ride a swing
after such a long time.

14:39.984 --> 14:42.778
How did you get any free time?

14:44.447 --> 14:46.365
I have something to ask you.

14:49.035 --> 14:50.744
CHA YOUGYUM

14:53.956 --> 14:55.332
It's grated yam.

14:55.333 --> 14:57.792
I did some research,
and they said it helps.

14:59.754 --> 15:03.215
Why was your tumbler
in my grandma's study?

15:03.216 --> 15:04.507
Huh?

15:04.508 --> 15:05.801
Oh… Well…

15:06.302 --> 15:08.971
I ran into her a while ago in the park.

15:09.805 --> 15:13.308
I left my tumbler behind,
and I guess she kept it for me.

15:13.309 --> 15:15.394
Grandma lied and said it was hers.

15:20.024 --> 15:22.360
You keep bringing up my grandma
for no reason,

15:23.194 --> 15:25.321
and you've been behaving strangely
these days.

15:26.364 --> 15:27.448
What was first?

15:28.115 --> 15:29.659
My grandma?

15:32.453 --> 15:33.454
Or Han Sora?

15:34.413 --> 15:35.414
What?

15:35.915 --> 15:37.792
Why are you suddenly mentioning Han Sora?

15:40.336 --> 15:43.506
Park Yeseul…
Why did she have to bring up Han Sora?

15:44.465 --> 15:45.840
Should I give him a snack?

15:49.887 --> 15:52.013
SORA

15:54.016 --> 15:55.934
Hey, Yougyum. It's me, Han Sora.

15:55.935 --> 15:57.811
What are you doing after practice?

15:57.812 --> 15:59.063
What about you?

16:01.107 --> 16:04.192
Her number was saved on your phone
with a heart.

16:04.193 --> 16:06.027
She just saved it without asking.

16:06.028 --> 16:08.530
I only found out the day she saved it.

16:08.531 --> 16:09.782
So you did meet her.

16:10.324 --> 16:11.325
Well…

16:13.035 --> 16:15.996
I did, but I actually…

16:17.206 --> 16:18.665
Hadam, it wasn't like that.

16:18.666 --> 16:20.667
She kept following me when I told her--

16:20.668 --> 16:22.502
"You're too young to marry."

16:22.503 --> 16:24.087
"Quit the nonsense."

16:24.088 --> 16:27.340
Did Grandma summon you
and threaten you or something?

16:27.341 --> 16:30.135
Why would you say that?
You know she wouldn't do such a thing.

16:30.136 --> 16:31.970
You and Grandma both deceived me.

16:31.971 --> 16:33.763
What are you hiding from me?

16:33.764 --> 16:36.975
Did she throw water at you,
telling you not to disrupt my studies?

16:36.976 --> 16:39.227
Did you get annoyed
and decide to meet Han Sora?

16:39.228 --> 16:40.438
Don't say that!

16:42.148 --> 16:44.316
Don't you know your own grandma?

16:44.317 --> 16:46.485
- Don't you know me?
- I don't!

16:52.199 --> 16:54.659
I met her to try to win
some brownie points,

16:54.660 --> 16:56.912
and I met Han Sora
to tell her I'm marrying you

16:57.788 --> 16:59.622
and that I'll report her as a stalker.

16:59.623 --> 17:01.583
I told her to get lost.

17:01.584 --> 17:04.253
That's all I said.
I only spoke to her for one minute.

17:05.212 --> 17:07.547
It's nothing like what you think--

17:07.548 --> 17:08.674
No.

17:09.258 --> 17:10.384
I don't believe you.

17:11.677 --> 17:14.721
I just can't believe
that you hid something from me.

17:16.349 --> 17:17.849
You feel like a stranger to me.

17:17.850 --> 17:20.227
What are you talking about?

17:22.355 --> 17:23.356
Fine.

17:24.023 --> 17:26.984
I couldn't tell you,
but that was only because of one thing.

17:29.278 --> 17:30.571
I was afraid you'd get hurt.

17:31.989 --> 17:32.990
But how…

17:37.578 --> 17:38.662
Why are you crying?

17:38.663 --> 17:40.580
I'm the one who should be crying.

17:40.581 --> 17:42.792
Did I not mean anything to you?

17:43.376 --> 17:44.877
It's you and me, Hadam.

17:45.628 --> 17:48.338
- This is just something trivial--
- Trivial?

17:48.339 --> 17:50.090
Is this trivial to you?

17:50.091 --> 17:51.591
No, Hadam. I didn't mean--

17:51.592 --> 17:52.967
If you were me…

17:54.470 --> 17:58.056
If people were gossiping
about me seeing another guy,

17:58.057 --> 18:00.725
then you see his name
saved with a heart on my phone,

18:00.726 --> 18:02.603
and I keep hiding things from you…

18:03.771 --> 18:05.439
- Then wouldn't you--
- No.

18:06.357 --> 18:08.567
No matter what people say about you,

18:09.694 --> 18:12.488
I only trust what I've seen
and the Hadam I know.

18:13.698 --> 18:14.824
That's the difference…

18:18.285 --> 18:19.286
between you and me.

18:22.123 --> 18:24.291
I'm sorry,
but I can't walk you home today.

18:35.636 --> 18:36.971
Ms. Song!

18:46.689 --> 18:47.897
Oh…

18:47.898 --> 18:49.482
It's you, Mr. Yeon.

18:49.483 --> 18:50.608
Pardon?

18:50.609 --> 18:51.693
It's nothing.

18:51.694 --> 18:53.863
I just reported this to Ms. Kim,

18:54.613 --> 18:56.824
but I got an email a moment ago

18:57.616 --> 18:58.701
from Producer Ben.

19:03.539 --> 19:05.874
All the other projects
have been canceled,

19:05.875 --> 19:08.418
and it's not looking good
for Ben's team either.

19:08.419 --> 19:10.795
Seeing how he asked
to halt the collaboration,

19:10.796 --> 19:12.882
it'll be difficult to resume the project.

19:13.924 --> 19:15.801
ANIMATOR SEONU CHAN

19:17.553 --> 19:20.346
The number you have dialed is unavailable.

19:20.347 --> 19:21.849
Please leave your message--

19:24.393 --> 19:26.227
You can use me as a friend
when you're bored

19:26.228 --> 19:27.896
or a misunderstanding for Ms. Kim.

19:27.897 --> 19:29.607
Just try me out as a free trial.

19:30.191 --> 19:33.234
As soon as the three months is over,

19:33.235 --> 19:34.820
I'll disappear without a trace.

19:39.492 --> 19:42.369
What kind of trial
ends so suddenly like this?

19:50.920 --> 19:52.796
What was that look Mr. Yeon gave me?

19:52.797 --> 19:54.881
He's so warm and friendly
to everyone else.

19:54.882 --> 19:56.592
Why is he so cold to me?

20:05.684 --> 20:07.478
Everything's a mess already,

20:07.978 --> 20:09.271
and now our house, too?

20:10.147 --> 20:11.439
Song Hayeong.

20:11.440 --> 20:12.816
I almost slipped on this.

20:12.817 --> 20:16.194
What? You didn't fall.

20:16.195 --> 20:19.531
-  Just clean this up.
- I'll clean it later.

20:19.532 --> 20:21.366
Just go do your thing.

20:21.367 --> 20:22.826
When is "later"?

20:22.827 --> 20:24.994
It's always when someone
cleans up after you.

20:24.995 --> 20:27.705
Always? Why would you say that?

20:27.706 --> 20:29.958
Do you think
I never clean up after myself?

20:29.959 --> 20:33.753
Stop being childish
and clean up your own mess.

20:33.754 --> 20:35.547
Yes, ma'am.

20:35.548 --> 20:37.048
Song Hayeong.

20:37.049 --> 20:40.094
I'm taking a short nap,
so please be quiet.

20:40.761 --> 20:42.637
I'm coming back in five minutes,
so clean this.

20:42.638 --> 20:44.722
I said I'll clean it later.

20:44.723 --> 20:46.058
You didn't even fall down.

20:48.018 --> 20:49.061
What did you just say?

20:52.356 --> 20:54.483
Yougyum, let's talk…

20:59.405 --> 21:00.780
Say that again.

21:00.781 --> 21:03.199
It's okay if I didn't fall down?

21:03.200 --> 21:05.618
Why are you taking
your anger out on me?

21:05.619 --> 21:07.370
Go take it out
on the person who upset you.

21:07.371 --> 21:08.788
Why are you picking a fight?

21:08.789 --> 21:10.456
You're the one who caused it.

21:10.457 --> 21:13.418
You clearly caused this,
and I'm the victim here.

21:13.419 --> 21:15.461
If you're so logical,
you should've been a lawyer.

21:15.462 --> 21:17.714
- Why did you become a designer?
- Hey!

21:17.715 --> 21:19.757
You two are so childish.

21:19.758 --> 21:21.634
Haven't you two aged at all?

21:21.635 --> 21:23.928
Can't you be quiet for 30 minutes?

21:23.929 --> 21:25.597
If you want to fight, go downstairs.

21:25.598 --> 21:27.473
You sleep downstairs.

21:27.474 --> 21:28.850
Being a high school senior
isn't everything.

21:28.851 --> 21:31.394
When did you ever show
any consideration for me?

21:31.395 --> 21:34.148
You never did anything
to help me with my studies!

21:34.648 --> 21:36.566
Forget it.

21:36.567 --> 21:39.068
What would I expect
from such immature people?

21:39.069 --> 21:40.778
There's no point talking to you.

21:44.283 --> 21:45.491
Song Hadam!

21:45.492 --> 21:47.869
You shouldn't be so mean
just because you're angry.

21:47.870 --> 21:50.204
Then why were you so mean to me?

21:50.205 --> 21:51.206
You…

21:52.249 --> 21:55.377
Forget it. Just clean this up.

22:01.592 --> 22:02.718
Did you just…

22:04.720 --> 22:06.013
- throw that at me?
-  Ah.

22:06.597 --> 22:07.847
Sorry.

22:07.848 --> 22:10.683
I was trying to clean it up,
but my hand slipped.

22:10.684 --> 22:12.144
If you're so upset, throw it back.

22:14.313 --> 22:16.022
I threw it like you said.

22:16.023 --> 22:18.816
You're not the only one
who can be stubborn, you know.

22:18.817 --> 22:21.235
That's not being stubborn.
It's being crazy.

22:24.365 --> 22:25.865
- Hey!
- What?

22:25.866 --> 22:27.159
You…

22:46.220 --> 22:48.013
What am I even doing?

23:00.985 --> 23:01.986
You cleaned it up.

23:02.569 --> 23:03.570
Yes.

23:05.572 --> 23:07.949
Are you… going somewhere?

23:07.950 --> 23:10.327
Yes, I'm going there.

23:11.453 --> 23:12.829
What's with the car key?

23:12.830 --> 23:14.081
I was about to go there, too.

23:15.499 --> 23:16.875
Should we go together?

23:17.751 --> 23:18.877
Fine.

23:19.712 --> 23:20.879
But just us?

23:21.964 --> 23:25.758
E raised to the power of 3in
equals negative c plus one.

23:25.759 --> 23:28.344
So for both sides to be equal,

23:28.345 --> 23:30.680
c should be 0, and d should be 1.

23:30.681 --> 23:33.766
Then hx to the power of x is negative 2…

23:33.767 --> 23:36.269
We're going to go there.

23:36.270 --> 23:37.812
If you want to join…

23:37.813 --> 23:43.776
Applying this formula
would give you x squared minus 2x plus 1.

23:43.777 --> 23:45.528
Did you get that?

23:45.529 --> 23:46.779
And…

24:00.127 --> 24:01.795
There are people passing by.

24:02.296 --> 24:04.130
It's so pretty.

24:04.131 --> 24:06.300
The ocean's beautiful.

24:16.018 --> 24:18.811
- I ended things with Yougyum.
- Huh?

24:18.812 --> 24:19.979
- What?
- Why?

24:19.980 --> 24:21.607
Should we try talking to him?

24:22.733 --> 24:25.027
We never argued before,

24:25.611 --> 24:27.945
but we cried and shouted at each other.

24:27.946 --> 24:30.616
So I can't even focus on studying.

24:31.617 --> 24:35.161
At this rate,
I'll mess up on the CSAT as well.

24:35.162 --> 24:38.122
My life is ruined.

24:40.626 --> 24:43.878
Did you just laugh? This is serious.

24:43.879 --> 24:47.548
I'm facing the biggest crisis
of my life right now.

24:47.549 --> 24:51.136
My gosh. Arguing with your boyfriend twice
might destroy the entire planet.

24:53.430 --> 24:55.515
You were acting like a grown-up,

24:55.516 --> 24:57.433
- but I guess you're still a baby.
- Hey.

24:57.434 --> 24:58.727
What did you two argue about?

25:00.687 --> 25:03.482
There was
a small misunderstanding…

25:04.108 --> 25:06.318
It's obvious
that it was your fault.

25:06.860 --> 25:08.528
He did something wrong, too.

25:08.529 --> 25:12.115
You should've seen his face.
How could he look at me like that?

25:13.659 --> 25:16.995
And, Hayeong,
what were you so pissed about?

25:20.040 --> 25:21.250
I don't know.

25:22.126 --> 25:24.460
It wasn't even anything serious.

25:24.461 --> 25:25.754
Why did I get so upset?

25:26.588 --> 25:27.672
It's a mystery.

25:27.673 --> 25:29.006
What?

25:29.007 --> 25:31.260
I know. It's weird.

25:31.927 --> 25:34.054
Anyway, I'm fine now.

25:34.847 --> 25:36.222
So it's a pass.

25:36.223 --> 25:37.807
What about you, then?

25:37.808 --> 25:41.185
What made you
throw snacks at me like that?

25:41.186 --> 25:43.897
What? She threw snacks at you?

25:44.857 --> 25:47.108
I missed a fun event.

25:47.109 --> 25:51.154
"Everything's a mess already."
Weren't you talking about yourself?

25:51.155 --> 25:53.948
I guess I just felt a bit upset.

25:53.949 --> 25:56.159
What's going on? Huh?

25:56.160 --> 25:57.577
What is it?

25:57.578 --> 25:59.079
It's just…

25:59.913 --> 26:02.540
My spring picnic ended too early.

26:02.541 --> 26:05.084
Geez. What are you saying?

26:05.085 --> 26:07.420
I hate it when people talk in riddles.

26:07.421 --> 26:08.630
Just be straightforward…

26:12.092 --> 26:13.093
It's cold.

26:13.677 --> 26:15.512
I should stick close to you for a bit.

26:16.346 --> 26:17.638
Let's go if you're cold.

26:17.639 --> 26:19.474
No, I want to stay a bit longer.

26:20.851 --> 26:23.769
Why is it so cold?

26:41.163 --> 26:42.873
Are you sure you're all right?

26:43.457 --> 26:44.665
Me?

26:44.666 --> 26:46.083
I'm fine.

26:46.084 --> 26:47.752
I'm always fine.

26:47.753 --> 26:50.338
I should be asking you that. Are you okay?

26:50.339 --> 26:51.340
Yes.

26:52.174 --> 26:53.217
I'll be fine.

26:54.134 --> 26:55.761
And I want to be fine.

26:57.346 --> 26:59.097
So I'm going to be okay.

27:00.265 --> 27:03.810
All right. I hope you will.

27:04.937 --> 27:08.732
Oh. I actually liked it
when we fought, though.

27:09.358 --> 27:10.692
It reminded me of old times.

27:13.946 --> 27:15.572
Chan's a really good guy.

27:16.615 --> 27:17.698
Huh?

27:17.699 --> 27:20.577
You'd normally never drink
on a business trip.

27:21.787 --> 27:24.539
So I asked Raemee
about what happened in Gyeongju.

27:26.249 --> 27:29.251
I'm sure Chan will get in touch soon.

27:30.462 --> 27:31.630
So let's just wait.

27:37.678 --> 27:39.554
It's called an iridescent cloud.

27:40.514 --> 27:43.976
They say you have good luck
if you see an iridescent cloud.

27:44.977 --> 27:49.855
You should look for iridescent clouds
in the sky, too,

27:49.856 --> 27:51.357
instead of just vapor trails.

27:58.949 --> 28:00.867
I guess that was fake, too.

28:02.411 --> 28:03.704
ADD NEW WALLPAPER

28:20.303 --> 28:21.513
It's okay.

28:22.597 --> 28:24.015
Good morning.

28:24.016 --> 28:25.683
It's not a good morning.

28:25.684 --> 28:27.101
Our animation collaboration--

28:27.102 --> 28:29.354
I heard. It's too bad.

28:30.022 --> 28:32.732
Je Raemee, can we do the concept meeting?

28:32.733 --> 28:34.066
Huh?

28:34.067 --> 28:35.151
Sure.

28:35.152 --> 28:36.695
Then let's begin in 10 minutes.

28:42.576 --> 28:44.785
"It's too bad"?

28:44.786 --> 28:45.996
That's it?

28:47.706 --> 28:51.125
We even went on a trip
to Gyeongju together.

28:51.126 --> 28:52.878
Doesn't she feel upset?

28:53.503 --> 28:54.587
ARCHIVES

28:54.588 --> 28:56.756
You must have cleaned out the archives.

28:56.757 --> 28:58.008
When did you find all this?

28:58.508 --> 29:00.009
I came pretty early today.

29:00.010 --> 29:03.387
I was looking through the material, and…

29:03.388 --> 29:04.680
You can take it.

29:04.681 --> 29:05.807
Sorry.

29:06.933 --> 29:09.018
Hmm? It's not mine.

29:09.019 --> 29:10.437
Oh.

29:12.147 --> 29:13.398
It's just spam.

29:14.316 --> 29:17.359
Anyway,
although this is a reinterpretation,

29:17.360 --> 29:18.903
I'd like a fresh twist…

29:18.904 --> 29:21.322
One, you're really okay.

29:21.323 --> 29:24.158
Two, you're pretending to be okay.

29:24.159 --> 29:26.619
Which is it?
You're not even checking your phone.

29:26.620 --> 29:27.745
You two were close--

29:27.746 --> 29:30.456
Why wouldn't I be okay?
We haven't known each other long.

29:30.457 --> 29:32.458
You're as cold as dry ice.

29:32.459 --> 29:34.461
You're so cold.

29:35.128 --> 29:37.589
I take back the 3.5 points.
You're zero points.

29:38.632 --> 29:41.592
Anyway, if you look at these photos,

29:41.593 --> 29:44.678
they seem pretty fresh even though
they're from 40 to 50 years ago.

29:44.679 --> 29:47.473
So instead of struggling
to create something new…

29:52.646 --> 29:54.396
Hi.

29:54.397 --> 29:56.690
Hey. Come and sit.

29:56.691 --> 29:58.151
- Do you want some coffee?
- Yes.

29:59.361 --> 30:01.279
You're not sitting by the window?

30:01.571 --> 30:03.406
This is my usual seat.

30:04.157 --> 30:06.660
Wait, was I acting like I own this place?

30:07.536 --> 30:11.705
By the way, it seems like the project
we were doing will be canceled.

30:11.706 --> 30:13.750
Then Chan won't come back?

30:15.001 --> 30:16.127
Probably not.

30:16.128 --> 30:18.672
I thought I should tell you
since you've been waiting.

30:20.006 --> 30:21.383
Then he could've told me…

30:31.643 --> 30:33.436
CALCULUS

30:37.149 --> 30:39.984
Wow. I've never seen Yougyum
wearing glasses before.

30:39.985 --> 30:41.068
He looks so good.

30:41.069 --> 30:43.697
-  Right?
-  He's so handsome.

30:46.408 --> 30:49.493
I only trust what I've seen
and the Hadam I know.

30:49.494 --> 30:51.829
That's the difference between you and me.

30:51.830 --> 30:53.330
He's so handsome.

30:53.331 --> 30:55.249
I can't believe it.

30:55.250 --> 30:56.667
I wish I could date him.

30:56.668 --> 30:58.420
Gosh, I'm so into him.

31:00.338 --> 31:01.922
Has his eyesight gotten bad?

31:01.923 --> 31:04.384
It'll be uncomfortable
playing with glasses on.

31:07.012 --> 31:09.139
What does it matter? We broke up anyway.

31:15.979 --> 31:19.523
Here's the operations report
you asked for last time.

31:19.524 --> 31:20.859
You're done already?

31:24.613 --> 31:25.696
Ah.

31:25.697 --> 31:28.199
It's too bad
the animation project got canceled.

31:28.200 --> 31:31.410
I'm actually glad
I can focus more on our next season.

31:31.411 --> 31:33.413
Call me if there's anything else you need.

32:00.649 --> 32:03.025
Should we bring the curve down
another 0.3 mm?

32:03.026 --> 32:07.029
And I think we should lower the neckline
by 0.5 mm as well.

32:07.030 --> 32:08.198
Then along the V-neck…

32:10.450 --> 32:11.576
What is this?

32:17.290 --> 32:18.458
It's so funny.

32:21.419 --> 32:24.339
The number you have dialed
is unavailable. Please leave--

32:24.923 --> 32:26.258
It's still turned off.

32:27.092 --> 32:29.301
She didn't even come to work.
Where is she?

32:29.302 --> 32:32.638
Isn't she in the storage room?
She's been going there before work.

32:32.639 --> 32:34.265
Her bag's not in her office.

32:34.266 --> 32:35.517
I don't think she even came here.

32:36.351 --> 32:38.228
Oh? She sent an email.

32:40.272 --> 32:42.898
"I'm sorry. I have to take a day off,

32:42.899 --> 32:45.776
so I'm sharing what I was planning
to cover in our meeting."

32:45.777 --> 32:49.405
What? Has she ever taken a day off before?

32:49.406 --> 32:51.282
Why didn't she keep her phone on?

32:51.283 --> 32:53.659
It's like she was determined to go AWOL.

32:53.660 --> 32:54.661
Go AWOL…

33:00.166 --> 33:01.542
Ms. Kim, Haran…

33:01.543 --> 33:02.877
Knock!

33:04.587 --> 33:07.089
Ms. Kim, why did Haran
suddenly take a day off?

33:07.090 --> 33:09.759
She has the right to take a day off.
Is there a problem?

33:10.343 --> 33:14.388
No,
but I think there's something wrong…

33:14.389 --> 33:18.183
I'm not sure, but it was strange
how she threw those snacks.

33:18.184 --> 33:19.351
And she said something

33:19.352 --> 33:22.021
about her picnic ending
and everything being a mess.

33:22.022 --> 33:23.981
You're the one who seems like a mess.

33:23.982 --> 33:25.858
What I mean is…

33:25.859 --> 33:27.861
Aren't you worried about her, Grandma?

33:28.820 --> 33:29.821
No.

33:30.322 --> 33:32.281
She's not a kid. She'll be fine.

33:32.282 --> 33:33.992
Go. Don't bother me.

33:35.493 --> 33:38.997
Where the heck is she?

33:47.756 --> 33:50.133
Your daughter's growing up, isn't she?

33:52.761 --> 33:54.346
LEAVE REQUEST FORM
SONG HARAN

34:01.978 --> 34:03.146
Hello.

34:04.272 --> 34:05.690
I'll be there on time.

34:07.108 --> 34:09.152
Yes,
we're scheduled to ship today.

34:09.778 --> 34:12.113
If the Lafayette customers respond well…

34:21.706 --> 34:24.458
You've been
to the dementia care center,

34:24.459 --> 34:26.543
- so we'll start with a screening test.
- Okay.

34:26.544 --> 34:28.171
Don't you have
a guardian with you?

34:30.256 --> 34:31.465
No.

34:31.466 --> 34:33.092
We'll call you when it's your turn.

34:33.093 --> 34:34.094
All right.

34:40.016 --> 34:42.601
What? If this isn't urgent--

34:42.602 --> 34:45.646
Didn't you confirm the Brulee Coat
as a one-button?

34:45.647 --> 34:47.648
Yes, a one-button. Why?

34:47.649 --> 34:50.692
The QC report for the factory
was stamped as a pass,

34:50.693 --> 34:52.945
but there's no button in the sample.

34:52.946 --> 34:55.115
We have less than four hours left
before shipment.

34:56.699 --> 35:00.245
Contact the Seongsu-dong factory.
I'll be there soon.

35:02.330 --> 35:03.873
How did I make such a mistake?

35:07.127 --> 35:10.046
SUNYUL NATIONAL UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

35:12.257 --> 35:13.549
Ms. Kim Nabong!

35:13.550 --> 35:14.843
Wait, Na…

35:15.593 --> 35:17.761
Ms. Kim Nabong?

35:17.762 --> 35:18.930
Nabong!

35:26.813 --> 35:27.814
Nabong!

35:28.440 --> 35:29.441
Nabong!

35:34.696 --> 35:35.697
What…

35:36.406 --> 35:37.741
What was she doing here?

35:39.743 --> 35:41.118
How much time do we have?

35:41.119 --> 35:42.202
Two hours.

35:42.203 --> 35:44.414
This won't work.
We should negotiate postponing--

35:45.582 --> 35:47.083
No, I'm not negotiating anything.

35:47.834 --> 35:50.794
If I can't keep our promises,
then I'm not fit to make clothes.

35:50.795 --> 35:53.672
I mistook it for a no-button coat,
so I'll fix this.

35:57.010 --> 35:59.345
We're adding buttons to all 70 coats.

36:00.263 --> 36:01.972
Bring them when they're done.

36:01.973 --> 36:04.100
I'll be checking each piece myself.

36:14.110 --> 36:15.361
-  Pass.
-  Pass.

36:18.156 --> 36:19.157
Again.

36:20.408 --> 36:21.409
Pass. Pass.

36:23.870 --> 36:26.372
We have
an hour and 10 minutes until shipment.

36:34.798 --> 36:36.007
Thank you.

36:38.468 --> 36:41.053
The shipment to Paris
has just been loaded.

36:42.514 --> 36:43.972
- What a relief.
- We did it.

36:43.973 --> 36:45.265
I'm so glad.

36:56.110 --> 36:57.194
I'm sorry.

36:57.195 --> 36:59.988
I made you work twice
because of my mistake.

36:59.989 --> 37:02.617
If it weren't for you,
we wouldn't have made them on time.

37:03.201 --> 37:04.619
Great job, everyone.

37:13.795 --> 37:15.255
I'm sorry. It was my mistake.

37:16.422 --> 37:18.715
I should have checked it
before the final sample.

37:18.716 --> 37:21.177
That's enough. It was clearly my mistake.

37:21.719 --> 37:25.931
And don't tell the design team about this.
There's no need to alarm them.

37:25.932 --> 37:27.183
Yes, ma'am.

37:27.684 --> 37:28.851
I'll drive you home.

37:30.687 --> 37:31.855
It's fine.

37:32.355 --> 37:34.106
Treat the factory workers to a meal…

37:34.107 --> 37:36.359
I booked a restaurant
and gave them expenses.

37:37.360 --> 37:38.361
I'd like

37:39.195 --> 37:41.072
to take you home today.

37:43.157 --> 37:44.701
I just want to walk for a bit.

37:45.368 --> 37:46.452
You can go.

38:11.728 --> 38:15.690
Whatever it is, I don't want you
to bear everything on your own.

38:16.441 --> 38:18.359
You can tell me anything, Ms. Kim.

38:46.888 --> 38:50.767
Hey, Hadam. Is Haran home?
She didn't call either?

38:52.769 --> 38:56.731
I'm on my way home,
but there's a lot of traffic…

38:59.525 --> 39:00.609
Huh?

39:00.610 --> 39:02.028
Hang on.

39:09.285 --> 39:10.703
Was I mistaken?

39:24.467 --> 39:26.594
Huh? Why are they sleeping here?

39:27.220 --> 39:28.429
Shh.

39:31.724 --> 39:33.893
They passed out
while waiting for you.

39:34.852 --> 39:37.230
So I was the culprit.

39:42.527 --> 39:44.862
It's late. Go and get some sleep.

39:46.823 --> 39:47.865
Good night.

39:54.247 --> 39:55.707
But why aren't you asking

39:56.416 --> 39:59.418
why I took the day off
or what I did all day?

39:59.419 --> 40:00.712
You're here, so it's fine.

40:01.295 --> 40:03.506
But next time,
write a proper form when taking a leave.

40:05.049 --> 40:06.467
It's not an art class, you know.

40:07.260 --> 40:09.469
Don't scribble on the request form.

40:09.470 --> 40:11.555
It wasn't a joke…

40:11.556 --> 40:12.974
A butterfly knot.

40:14.142 --> 40:16.269
You needed time to get some closure…

40:17.103 --> 40:18.521
on Seonu Chan.

40:20.565 --> 40:23.191
Normally, you'd never
go on a business trip a day early.

40:23.192 --> 40:26.320
And the expressions on your face
in the videos…

40:27.655 --> 40:30.867
I guess… you grew more attached to him
than I thought,

40:31.534 --> 40:33.494
seeing how you needed time for closure.

40:36.205 --> 40:37.206
I just…

40:37.999 --> 40:40.209
wanted to be okay.

40:43.296 --> 40:45.590
When we first met, he told me

40:46.883 --> 40:50.344
that it seemed like
I was trapped in winter.

40:51.679 --> 40:52.804
Thank you.

40:52.805 --> 40:54.056
-  Thank you for these.
-  Enjoy.

40:54.057 --> 40:55.224
Thank you.

40:59.103 --> 41:02.189
Don't you crave croissants
when you see the crescent moon?

41:02.190 --> 41:06.402
I didn't want to get trapped
in winter again, so I wanted to be okay,

41:07.028 --> 41:09.363
but it didn't go well.

41:11.741 --> 41:13.366
I forgot to buy this.

41:13.367 --> 41:15.202
It's my favorite.

41:15.203 --> 41:16.454
Take this.

41:17.872 --> 41:19.749
Whatever I do, whatever I see,

41:20.833 --> 41:22.543
I keep getting reminded of him.

41:23.336 --> 41:25.962
There are 0.3, 0.4, 5, 6,

41:25.963 --> 41:28.758
oil-based, water-based,
nib tip, and ballpoint pens.

41:30.259 --> 41:32.344
SEONU CHAN

41:33.805 --> 41:38.351
I couldn't figure out
a way to be okay,

41:39.519 --> 41:41.020
but then I found this.

41:42.021 --> 41:43.647
SEOUL DESTINATIONS LIST

41:43.648 --> 41:45.858
Choose where to go first
so we can go together later.

41:47.110 --> 41:51.072
So I thought I'd have some closure
if I checked off the whole list.

41:51.697 --> 41:56.535
This could be the final knot.

41:56.536 --> 41:57.786
-  What about this?
-  This?

41:57.787 --> 42:00.123
-  Can I try this?
-  It looks good on you.

42:01.624 --> 42:03.876
How should I choose?

42:08.339 --> 42:11.216
Sorry, but could you take a photo of us?

42:12.301 --> 42:13.385
- We'll take one for you, too.
- Thank you.

42:13.386 --> 42:14.678
Oh, I'm okay.

42:14.679 --> 42:15.847
Thank you.

42:17.140 --> 42:19.766
So I went sightseeing
here and there

42:19.767 --> 42:22.018
and tried a lot of things…

42:31.737 --> 42:34.824
But I kept feeling bored, for some reason.

42:36.075 --> 42:41.664
Everything I did with him
was just so fun and exciting,

42:42.540 --> 42:45.626
so I thought it would be fun
to do whatever was on the list.

42:48.504 --> 42:49.630
Haran.

42:51.340 --> 42:55.260
People, relationships, and even memories

42:55.261 --> 42:59.098
could disappear tomorrow
if you let them slip through your hands.

43:00.099 --> 43:02.018
Go to the US and see him.

43:02.602 --> 43:05.228
Whether you become okay or not,
get it sorted.

43:05.229 --> 43:07.315
You can easily meet him if you want to.

43:08.524 --> 43:12.652
No, we were never that close
to begin with.

43:12.653 --> 43:13.862
That would be silly.

43:13.863 --> 43:19.660
There's nothing as sad and stupid
as regretting things

43:20.536 --> 43:22.329
after time has passed.

43:22.330 --> 43:25.333
Life is too short
to spend it on regretting things.

43:26.375 --> 43:28.920
He was going to go back anyway.

43:29.545 --> 43:31.130
He just left earlier than planned.

43:33.716 --> 43:36.343
This is why I didn't want
to get close to anyone.

43:36.344 --> 43:37.678
So do you regret it?

43:39.222 --> 43:42.683
Do you regret getting to know Mr. Seonu?

43:45.728 --> 43:46.771
I do…

43:48.147 --> 43:49.273
have regrets.

43:50.691 --> 43:52.652
If I knew he'd leave so quickly,

43:53.236 --> 43:54.445
I would have been…

43:56.447 --> 43:57.572
kinder to him.

44:00.534 --> 44:03.037
I was a bit mean to him at first.

44:04.538 --> 44:07.291
But I don't regret

44:08.668 --> 44:10.044
getting to know him.

44:10.628 --> 44:11.920
A three-month trial!

44:11.921 --> 44:13.338
There's nothing to lose.

44:13.339 --> 44:15.131
You can overcome it.

44:15.132 --> 44:16.801
Once you know how,

44:17.593 --> 44:19.887
you'll be able to escape on your own.

44:20.596 --> 44:25.559
I learned it through that person,
so I wanted to show you, too.

44:26.143 --> 44:28.062
Thanks to that weird trial,

44:29.480 --> 44:31.816
I learned how to escape on my own.

44:34.819 --> 44:37.530
So I know I met a great person.

44:40.533 --> 44:42.118
I feel grateful.

44:44.704 --> 44:46.914
Then that's enough.

45:03.973 --> 45:07.268
Traditional knots
each have a specific meaning.

45:08.436 --> 45:11.313
A new life, change…

45:11.314 --> 45:14.941
Sometimes, you have to free something
instead of clutching it tightly

45:14.942 --> 45:16.610
to open up a new beginning.

45:17.278 --> 45:20.489
That's what… this butterfly knot means.

45:34.420 --> 45:36.630
Is she not coming today either?

45:37.631 --> 45:40.425
Sorry, I'm late.
It took some time picking up bribes.

45:40.426 --> 45:42.093
- She's here.
- Ms. Song.

45:42.094 --> 45:44.262
I was late helping her carry this.

45:46.515 --> 45:49.017
This is an apology
for taking a leave without notice.

45:49.018 --> 45:51.478
-  Thanks.
-  Thank you.

45:51.479 --> 45:52.855
Didn't you bring mine?

45:53.439 --> 45:55.065
Of course, we did.

45:56.776 --> 46:00.029
Someone go visit Mr. Yoon's exhibit later.
I have plans today.

46:00.488 --> 46:01.489
I'll go.

46:04.116 --> 46:06.452
All right. Go and visit him.

46:07.661 --> 46:09.330
- Thanks for the coffee.
- Sure.

46:12.458 --> 46:14.459
-  Thank you.
-  Thank you.

46:14.460 --> 46:15.877
Drop by when you're free.

46:15.878 --> 46:17.838
There's another thing
waiting for its owner.

46:25.096 --> 46:26.097
Yes?

46:27.515 --> 46:29.808
I'll go with you.

46:29.809 --> 46:32.644
I thought you'd return
to your cold, distant self.

46:32.645 --> 46:33.813
I'm proud of you.

46:41.070 --> 46:42.113
Here.

46:43.072 --> 46:44.572
What is it this time?

46:44.573 --> 46:46.992
Did you find a flower ring
you were going to give me?

46:48.702 --> 46:51.288
I saw you when I was getting my checkup.

46:54.041 --> 46:55.542
Why were you at the hospital?

46:55.543 --> 46:57.043
Are you sick or anything?

46:57.044 --> 46:59.963
I was just visiting a friend there.

46:59.964 --> 47:03.300
Then what made you rush out like that?
You even dropped your hat.

47:04.677 --> 47:08.722
Something urgent came up at work,
so, of course, I wasn't skipping happily.

47:11.892 --> 47:13.226
Oh, right.

47:13.227 --> 47:15.563
Seonu Chan
didn't contact you either, did he?

47:16.230 --> 47:17.231
What?

47:18.315 --> 47:22.027
No, he didn't.
I'm actually worried about Haran, though.

47:22.736 --> 47:25.321
There seemed to be something
going on between them.

47:25.322 --> 47:28.826
I'm worried she'll end up in pain
like seven years ago.

47:29.410 --> 47:30.827
It won't happen again.

47:30.828 --> 47:33.456
She seems to have grown stronger
after spending time with him.

47:34.039 --> 47:37.251
Right. My roommate
was quite an incredible guy.

47:39.670 --> 47:41.005
I feel really grateful.

47:41.589 --> 47:43.048
It's such a shame.

47:49.388 --> 47:51.265
I loved the exhibit.

47:52.475 --> 47:54.058
Gosh, look at all these people.

47:54.059 --> 47:57.562
Being out here on a bustling street
makes me so excited!

48:03.903 --> 48:05.862
7:00 P.M. SAMCHEONG-DONG
TODAY 7:00 P.M.

48:05.863 --> 48:08.114
Ah. Mark that on your schedule.

48:08.115 --> 48:09.950
You'd better not forget or show up late.

48:13.662 --> 48:15.288
I totally forgot about this.

48:15.289 --> 48:17.124
Can't I cancel it?

48:19.752 --> 48:20.835
Oh, God!

48:20.836 --> 48:23.254
Isn't this restaurant
so, so, so famous

48:23.255 --> 48:27.134
that you have to wait for months
to book a table?

48:28.302 --> 48:29.762
Take me instead of canceling.

48:30.513 --> 48:32.555
There isn't much time left…

48:32.556 --> 48:34.224
It's just right over there.

48:34.225 --> 48:36.392
We can get there if we run.

48:36.393 --> 48:38.729
Come on!

48:44.735 --> 48:45.736
This is amazing.

48:47.029 --> 48:49.030
It's so nice and peaceful here.

48:57.665 --> 48:58.666
Yes, Ms. Kim.

48:59.333 --> 49:00.876
Yes, I saw him.

49:02.419 --> 49:04.796
I took a pamphlet, too.

49:07.258 --> 49:08.259
All right.

49:09.093 --> 49:10.219
Hello?

49:11.095 --> 49:12.763
Really? Okay.

49:14.557 --> 49:16.516
I'm really sorry.

49:16.517 --> 49:20.228
My partner's a soldier,
and he just got an unexpected leave.

49:20.229 --> 49:23.314
- So, I'm sorry, but I have to go.
- What?

49:23.315 --> 49:24.566
Enjoy your meal. Bye.

49:24.567 --> 49:26.067
I'm very sorry!

49:26.068 --> 49:27.819
What…

49:27.820 --> 49:29.196
Wait, your scarf…

49:29.822 --> 49:31.072
Je Raemee!

49:31.073 --> 49:32.907
Wait!

49:32.908 --> 49:35.326
Je Raemee, here!

49:35.327 --> 49:36.411
Your scarf…

49:36.412 --> 49:37.997
Give it to me next time.
Sorry!

49:42.084 --> 49:44.295
-  I'm sorry.
- It's okay, I'll do it.

49:44.962 --> 49:46.547
- Sorry.
- No problem.

49:54.555 --> 49:56.056
Why did I even come here?

50:09.737 --> 50:11.864
It's even snowing?

50:20.748 --> 50:21.957
Ms. Song!

50:26.545 --> 50:27.755
Hearing things again?

50:32.509 --> 50:33.552
Ms. Song!

51:03.248 --> 51:04.458
How have you been?

51:09.296 --> 51:11.715
I told you not to be late, but I'm late.

51:14.218 --> 51:16.345
Oh? Why do you look so frail?

51:17.304 --> 51:19.098
Did you not eat well?

51:19.932 --> 51:21.266
Has work been tough?

51:25.396 --> 51:27.523
Um… Well…

51:28.065 --> 51:29.565
Aren't you happy to see me?

51:29.566 --> 51:31.402
I'm so happy that I almost hugged…

51:34.154 --> 51:35.238
I mean…

51:36.907 --> 51:39.242
I almost did a backflip.

51:42.287 --> 51:43.871
Here. How about a high five instead?

51:43.872 --> 51:46.500
I usually do high fives
when I'm happy to see someone.

52:10.733 --> 52:12.317
I have a habit…

52:13.527 --> 52:15.362
of hugging people I'm happy to see.

52:34.631 --> 52:39.136
I promised that I'd be here by today,
no matter what.

52:54.651 --> 52:57.069
You messaged me? When?

52:57.070 --> 52:59.823
Didn't you come here
because of my message?

53:02.326 --> 53:04.535
Please wear your seatbelts

53:04.536 --> 53:08.373
and switch all electronic devices
to airplane mode.

53:10.626 --> 53:11.709
I'll be back soon.

53:11.710 --> 53:13.920
Even if the project gets canceled,
I'll be back soon.

53:13.921 --> 53:15.797
We said we'd have dinner together.

53:15.798 --> 53:17.089
I promise to be there by that day.

53:17.090 --> 53:18.841
Don't worry even if you can't reach me.

53:18.842 --> 53:21.093
Tell Mr. Park and everyone not to worry.

53:21.094 --> 53:22.553
Sir, we'll be taking off soon.

53:22.554 --> 53:24.430
- Please switch to airplane mode.
- Okay.

53:28.602 --> 53:30.937
It's on.

53:30.938 --> 53:31.939
Oh.

53:32.898 --> 53:34.065
Look, I sent it…

53:34.066 --> 53:36.568
Oh? What's this exclamation mark?

53:39.238 --> 53:41.114
It means it failed to send.

53:42.658 --> 53:46.702
Oh! If you didn't receive
my message, then you must have…

53:46.703 --> 53:49.206
You're here, so it's fine. Eat up.

53:56.255 --> 53:57.506
Have more of this.

54:02.761 --> 54:04.304
Here.

54:05.931 --> 54:07.348
Eat all of that, okay?

54:07.349 --> 54:09.141
This is why you're so thin.

54:09.142 --> 54:12.813
Are there no mirrors in the States?
You're the one who looks so gaunt.

54:13.397 --> 54:16.233
I should've dressed up a bit.

54:16.900 --> 54:18.401
It's been a while since we met.

54:20.946 --> 54:22.488
What about headquarters?

54:22.489 --> 54:24.825
Mr. Yeon said it's not looking so good.

54:25.450 --> 54:26.660
Oh, um…

54:28.078 --> 54:31.039
I'm not sure
how to tell you this,

54:31.999 --> 54:33.876
- but…
- It got canceled, right?

54:34.626 --> 54:37.045
Then do you have to go back soon?

54:38.213 --> 54:41.341
This is really important, so…

54:45.178 --> 54:48.098
I resolved everything really well.

54:54.438 --> 54:56.606
It's me, Seonu Chan.

54:56.607 --> 54:58.608
We've already visited the site.

54:58.609 --> 55:00.109
Seeing it in person, it's clear

55:00.110 --> 55:02.486
we can take this project
beyond the original idea.

55:02.487 --> 55:05.364
If anything needs adjusting,
we can move on it right away.

55:05.365 --> 55:06.824
No.

55:06.825 --> 55:09.745
It almost got canceled, but…

55:10.662 --> 55:14.081
I think Scene 27 feels
a bit flat. What do you think?

55:14.082 --> 55:17.376
I don't think it's about the sharpness,
it's about the keyframe timing.

55:17.377 --> 55:20.755
I don't think it's about impact.
The emotion isn't just coming through.

55:20.756 --> 55:23.924
Emergency meetings, back-to-back meetings,

55:23.925 --> 55:26.303
persuasion, even script revisions…

55:27.971 --> 55:30.682
Hey, uh…
how's the background coming along?

55:31.767 --> 55:35.436
Around 60 percent. But they want
another look at the main character.

55:35.437 --> 55:36.896
- At this point?
-  Yeah.

55:45.113 --> 55:46.197
Thank you.

55:48.617 --> 55:49.993
Yeah?

55:50.994 --> 55:53.245
Okay. We'll be right there.

55:53.246 --> 55:54.873
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

55:56.083 --> 55:58.668
Hey, they're asking for a script meeting.
Okay? Come on.

55:58.669 --> 56:00.544
We didn't want to give up, no matter what,

56:00.545 --> 56:04.340
so we all fought through it
with gritted teeth.

56:04.341 --> 56:07.385
We agreed to revise the parts
that had differing opinions.

56:07.386 --> 56:09.929
That's such a relief.

56:09.930 --> 56:11.889
You said you worked on it
for over two years.

56:11.890 --> 56:13.557
That's one thing…

56:13.558 --> 56:14.559
Mmm…

56:16.478 --> 56:19.064
But I really wanted to apply Won's costume

56:19.648 --> 56:22.859
that you made in the animation.

56:24.027 --> 56:27.239
And that's what got me through it.

56:32.911 --> 56:35.955
Let's eat up and go.
Mr. Park's been waiting for you.

56:35.956 --> 56:38.041
I want to spend more time with you.

56:39.459 --> 56:41.044
Can you stay out late tonight?

56:48.468 --> 56:50.845
I'll clear the table
and bring your dessert.

56:50.846 --> 56:51.929
Thank you.

56:51.930 --> 56:54.640
I should call Mr. Park.

56:59.396 --> 57:00.563
Mr. Park, I'm here.

57:00.564 --> 57:03.482
Genius, Chan is here!

57:03.483 --> 57:05.360
- Why are you crying?
- He's crying?

57:06.653 --> 57:08.446
I'm sorry I couldn't call.

57:08.447 --> 57:10.489
No, no. It's fine.

57:10.490 --> 57:13.242
I'm just so happy.

57:13.243 --> 57:15.328
I thought I'd never see you again.

57:16.079 --> 57:18.122
I was so upset.

57:18.123 --> 57:19.999
Don't cry.

57:20.000 --> 57:22.377
Now I can finally sleep easy.

57:26.006 --> 57:27.174
Yes.

57:28.967 --> 57:31.011
Yes. All right.

57:35.307 --> 57:38.143
Make sure to have dinner
and take your meds. I'll visit later.

57:38.769 --> 57:39.770
Okay.

57:41.563 --> 57:42.898
He was so excited, wasn't he?

57:44.441 --> 57:48.319
Mr. Park and the others
were waiting for you the whole time.

57:48.320 --> 57:53.532
Our whole team, Genius,
and even Donggu came looking for you.

57:53.533 --> 57:56.828
I'm so glad everything worked out.

57:57.537 --> 58:00.080
Only good things
will happen from now on.

58:00.081 --> 58:01.082
For real.

58:02.250 --> 58:04.961
Everything's going to be fine now.

58:05.629 --> 58:06.963
Everything's fine.

58:33.365 --> 58:34.866
JAY YOON 2ND EXHIBIT

58:42.374 --> 58:46.044
I missed you too,
but Haran would've had quite a hard time.

58:46.795 --> 58:49.213
You're the one
who gave her the camera, right?

58:49.214 --> 58:53.509
She seemed so excited
when she was taking the photos,

58:53.510 --> 58:56.345
but after you left,
her eyes were always bloodshot

58:56.346 --> 58:58.890
as if she wasn't sleeping well.

59:26.751 --> 59:29.920
We'll do this line.

59:29.921 --> 59:31.297
Please send us an email.

59:31.298 --> 59:32.299
All right.

59:32.966 --> 59:35.676
But is business not going well these days?

59:35.677 --> 59:37.052
Our company?

59:37.053 --> 59:41.932
Mr. Yeon came by in person yesterday,
so I wondered if anything's wrong.

59:41.933 --> 59:45.144
Why would he come here in person?

59:45.145 --> 59:47.563
He always paid upfront
when placing orders,

59:47.564 --> 59:50.190
but this time, he asked to pay afterward,

59:50.191 --> 59:52.276
saying he needed new materials.

59:52.277 --> 59:53.570
New materials…

59:54.988 --> 59:56.864
- Was it…
- Bio-silk.

59:56.865 --> 59:58.158
Fermented protein fabric.

01:00:01.953 --> 01:00:05.998
He said he didn't want money
to limit the designers' creativity.

01:00:05.999 --> 01:00:09.209
He asked us to get the material,
no matter what.

01:00:09.210 --> 01:00:10.961
It's been 10 years,

01:00:10.962 --> 01:00:13.423
but I've never seen him
ask for something so earnestly.

01:00:16.718 --> 01:00:20.180
- Mr. Yeon, where are you?
-  I'm on my way to a meeting.

01:00:24.392 --> 01:00:26.353
Wait! Stop!

01:00:31.942 --> 01:00:35.612
You rejected the idea at the meeting.
Why would you beg someone else to help?

01:00:36.279 --> 01:00:37.280
What…

01:00:38.823 --> 01:00:39.908
Ah.

01:00:40.659 --> 01:00:42.660
I only focus on reality during meetings.

01:00:42.661 --> 01:00:44.870
If I say it's possible
and it turns out it's not,

01:00:44.871 --> 01:00:48.207
the designers will end up
dealing with the consequences.

01:00:48.208 --> 01:00:50.293
You made me seem like an immature kid.

01:00:51.419 --> 01:00:55.298
If I'd known, I wouldn't have gone on
about all that protein fabric.

01:00:56.633 --> 01:01:00.219
It's okay, so you don't have
to go through all that trouble.

01:01:00.220 --> 01:01:02.763
It's really, really fine with me.

01:01:02.764 --> 01:01:06.475
So don't go anywhere pleading for help.

01:01:06.476 --> 01:01:07.894
Why are you…

01:01:09.437 --> 01:01:11.022
always saying you're okay?

01:01:12.524 --> 01:01:14.401
This is why I didn't tell you.

01:01:15.568 --> 01:01:18.321
I knew you'd say you're okay
when you're not.

01:01:20.448 --> 01:01:22.574
It's my job to take care of such issues.

01:01:22.575 --> 01:01:24.911
So you can be greedy about what you want

01:01:26.496 --> 01:01:28.289
and tell people…

01:01:29.332 --> 01:01:30.667
you're not okay

01:01:32.168 --> 01:01:33.169
when you're not.

01:01:40.176 --> 01:01:42.053
What…

01:01:47.058 --> 01:01:51.354
When did I keep saying I was okay?

01:02:03.742 --> 01:02:05.869
Mom…

01:02:17.505 --> 01:02:19.049
I have to be okay.

01:02:20.592 --> 01:02:22.385
I have to keep our family together.

01:02:26.848 --> 01:02:28.308
I have to be okay.

01:02:28.975 --> 01:02:31.478
I have to be okay.

01:02:36.483 --> 01:02:37.692
Mr. Yeon.

01:02:39.569 --> 01:02:40.695
I'm sorry.

01:02:42.072 --> 01:02:43.740
Why are you sorry?

01:02:44.407 --> 01:02:46.201
You're the first one to come here.

01:02:46.785 --> 01:02:49.161
Go and say goodbye to Mom and Dad.

01:02:49.162 --> 01:02:50.163
I'm sorry.

01:02:51.748 --> 01:02:52.874
I'm really sorry.

01:03:02.967 --> 01:03:05.302
I can't believe
I slept for an hour at a restaurant.

01:03:05.303 --> 01:03:06.471
You should've woken me.

01:03:07.180 --> 01:03:10.307
Huh? Wasn't that restaurant your home?

01:03:10.308 --> 01:03:12.601
You slept so comfortably,
I thought it was your house.

01:03:12.602 --> 01:03:16.063
I slept while you're the one
who took a 10-hour flight.

01:03:16.064 --> 01:03:17.898
Go home and get some sleep.

01:03:17.899 --> 01:03:20.109
No, I'm wide awake now.

01:03:20.110 --> 01:03:24.279
But didn't you come from the airport?
Where's all your luggage?

01:03:24.280 --> 01:03:25.489
What luggage?

01:03:26.699 --> 01:03:28.033
My suitcase!

01:03:28.034 --> 01:03:30.495
DEPARTURE TEAM 1

01:03:36.626 --> 01:03:40.212
All your important stuff must be in there.
How could you forget a whole bag?

01:03:40.213 --> 01:03:43.215
I was just in a hurry to make it on time.

01:03:43.216 --> 01:03:44.967
Don't worry.

01:03:44.968 --> 01:03:48.971
The lost and found system's pretty good,
so I'm sure I'll find it.

01:03:48.972 --> 01:03:52.016
Sir, please stop
in front of the coffee-colored gate.

01:03:53.143 --> 01:03:54.434
Tell me when you find it.

01:03:54.435 --> 01:03:57.813
Don't wait up for me.
I'll leave you a message if I find it.

01:03:57.814 --> 01:03:59.774
Uh…

01:04:00.316 --> 01:04:03.068
You might fall asleep in the yard
on the way inside.

01:04:03.069 --> 01:04:06.280
I'll go to SHIM tomorrow morning.

01:04:06.281 --> 01:04:08.741
Okay. I'll see you tomorrow, then.

01:04:15.039 --> 01:04:16.583
What a shame.

01:04:26.259 --> 01:04:29.136
I found it.

01:04:29.137 --> 01:04:31.305
DESIGNER SONG HARAN

01:04:31.306 --> 01:04:32.473
I'll see you tomorrow.

01:04:36.895 --> 01:04:39.855
I told you not to wait up.

01:04:39.856 --> 01:04:42.649
Did you check your stuff?
Is everything inside?

01:04:42.650 --> 01:04:43.651
Yes, I checked…

01:04:51.367 --> 01:04:52.535
That's great.

01:04:59.083 --> 01:05:01.960
Didn't you say you hated the first snow?

01:05:01.961 --> 01:05:03.212
The first snow?

01:05:03.213 --> 01:05:08.050
I did, but I feel like
I'll start hating it less now.

01:05:08.051 --> 01:05:09.135
But why do you ask?

01:05:10.637 --> 01:05:14.556
You said you hated it,
but you're wandering about outside.

01:05:14.557 --> 01:05:16.476
Do you even know where I am?

01:05:17.185 --> 01:05:18.603
Can you see me?

01:05:19.437 --> 01:05:20.438
Where are you?

01:05:20.939 --> 01:05:23.106
You said you were home…

01:05:23.107 --> 01:05:24.817
I thought I'd regret it.

01:05:27.654 --> 01:05:31.866
After you suddenly disappeared,
I had a lot of regrets.

01:05:32.492 --> 01:05:36.828
I kept remembering how harsh
I was on you when you were so nice to me.

01:05:38.873 --> 01:05:43.126
I don't want to have any more regrets,
so can you help me out?

01:05:48.424 --> 01:05:53.346
Is it okay if I be really nice
to you this time?

01:05:59.352 --> 01:06:00.812
I'll start today.

01:06:01.312 --> 01:06:03.731
I'll keep you company on the way to Seoul.

01:06:05.566 --> 01:06:07.902
But where are you?

01:06:09.529 --> 01:06:10.530
I found you.

01:06:19.539 --> 01:06:20.581
This is bad.

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:23.459
What? What's bad?

01:06:24.043 --> 01:06:26.170
I've been holding back until now…

01:06:27.672 --> 01:06:31.718
I can't even explain myself to you,

01:06:32.844 --> 01:06:36.431
and I shouldn't like you this much.

01:06:37.682 --> 01:06:40.684
- Your bag…
-  I shouldn't keep wanting you…

01:06:40.685 --> 01:06:43.479
- You should bring…
- …like this…

01:07:15.386 --> 01:07:16.553
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:07:40.578 --> 01:07:42.746
He spoke as if he knew me.

01:07:42.747 --> 01:07:47.542
I may not be as good
for Designer Song.

01:07:47.543 --> 01:07:49.336
You used to call him Chan.

01:07:49.337 --> 01:07:52.547
Your old boyfriend, Hyeokchan.

01:07:52.548 --> 01:07:54.801
Their names… were similar.

01:07:55.635 --> 01:07:58.345
How much do you know
about Haran's past?

01:07:58.346 --> 01:08:01.849
I'm sorry for leaving like that
and for hurting you.

01:08:02.600 --> 01:08:04.643
Why is this pen here?

01:08:04.644 --> 01:08:08.105
If I just play dumb
and be greedy until I go back,

01:08:08.106 --> 01:08:10.233
would that be wrong?

01:08:22.495 --> 01:08:23.578
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:08:23.579 --> 01:08:24.580
Translated by Juyoung Park
